      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CANYA DETONATOR (3) scored two back then drifted back and missed the frame latest finishing a 3.5 lengths 4th at Q Lakeside (25.74). The form out of last race has been strong. Has ability and can bounce back. ZIPPING TESFAY (6) scored well last start as odds-on favourite by 1.5 lengths at Q Parklands in a handy 29.91 beating Ellidy. Jumping from the pinch draw but likes the trip. Speedy beginner who can find the front despite the tricky draw. Form should stack up. PLAYING TO WIN (4) finds it hard to break through. Finished in the minors latest when third (24.04) at this track and may be close to breaking through. Solid beginner who can clear the tricky draw. Bold showing expected. RUN ZULU RUN (1) has been in the frame at his last two runs, most recently when second (24.50) in a Grade 6 over 407m at this track.",
